org.jsapar

Class Text2TextConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jsapar.convert.AbstractConverter
      • org.jsapar.Text2TextConverter
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConcurrentText2TextConverter

    public class Text2TextConverter
extends AbstractConverter
    Converts one text input to another text output. For instance converting from CSV to fixed with format. See AbstractConverter for details about error handling and manipulating data.
    See Also:

        public long convert(Reader reader,
                    Writer writer)
             throws IOException
        Converts text read from the reader according to the parse schema and writes the output to the writer according to the compose schema.
        Parameters:
        reader - The reader to read input from
        writer - The writer to write converted result to.
        Returns:
        Number of converted lines.
        Throws:
        IOException - In case of IO error
